  select(-region) # not needed since it will be all NC data now

Mapping Teen Pregnancy Rates

Rates in 2003

mapdata %>% 
  filter(year == 2003) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(aes(x = long, 
                   y = lat, 
                   group = group, 
                   fill = birth_rate),
               color = "black") +
  coord_map() +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "purple") +
  labs(title = "2003 Teen Birth Rates in North Carolina",
       caption = "Data Source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  no_axes_theme

mapdata %>% 
  filter(year == 2003) %>% 
  select(county, LCL, birth_rate, UCL) %>% 
  distinct() %>% # since there are repeated rows for mapping
  kable(col.names = c("County", "LCL", "Birth Rate", "UCL"),
        align = c("l", "c", "c", "c"),
        caption = "2003 Teen Birth Rates in NC") %>% 
  kable_styling(full_width = FALSE,
                position = "left",
                bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed"))

westernNCdata <- mapdata %>%
  filter(subregion %in% western) %>% 
  pivot_longer(c(LCL, birth_rate, UCL), 
               names_to = "statname", 
               values_to = "statvalue") %>% 
  distinct()
glimpse(westernNCdata)

westernNCdata %>% 
  filter(year == 2003) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = statvalue, y = reorder(county, -statvalue))) +
  geom_line(aes(group = county), linetype = "dotted") +
  geom_point(aes(color = statname)) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("black", "orange", "blue")) +
  labs(title = "2003 Teen Birth Rates in Western NC",
       x = "estimated teen birth rate with lower (LCL) and upper (UCL) confidence limits",
       y = "county") +
  theme_linedraw()
